dlinkSwDhcpServerMIB.name: dlinkSwDhcpServerMIB
dlinkSwDhcpServerMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwDhcpServerMIB.description: The MIB module for managing DHCP Server.

dDhcpServiceEnabled.name: dDhcpServiceEnabled
dDhcpServiceEnabled.description: This object enables/disables the DHCP server and relay service on the device.

dDhcpServerPingPktNumber.name: dDhcpServerPingPktNumber
dDhcpServerPingPktNumber.description: This object specifies the number of PING packets the DHCP server sends to an IP address before assigning this address to a requesting client. Setting this object to 0 will disable the PING operation.

dDhcpServerPingTimeOut.name: dDhcpServerPingTimeOut
dDhcpServerPingTimeOut.description: This object specifies the amount of time in millisecond the DHCP server must wait before timing out a ping packet. The specified value should be multiple of 100.

dDhcpSExcludedAddressTable.name: dDhcpSExcludedAddressTable
dDhcpSExcludedAddressTable.description: A list of configurations about a range of IP addresses that the DHCP server should not assign to DHCP client.

dDhcpSExcludedAddressEntry.name: dDhcpSExcludedAddressEntry
dDhcpSExcludedAddressEntry.description: An entry contaning information about an IP address range that the DHCP server should not assign to DHCP client.

dDhcpSExcludedAddressVrfName.name: dDhcpSExcludedAddressVrfName
dDhcpSExcludedAddressVrfName.description: The name of virtual routing and forwarding (VRF). When the VRF is not specified (zero length string), the corresponding configuration is used for global address space.

dDhcpSExcludedAddressBeginAddr.name: dDhcpSExcludedAddressBeginAddr
dDhcpSExcludedAddressBeginAddr.description: The first address of this address range.

dDhcpSExcludedAddressEndAddr.name: dDhcpSExcludedAddressEndAddr
dDhcpSExcludedAddressEndAddr.description: The last address of this address range.

dDhcpSExcludedAddressRowStatus.name: dDhcpSExcludedAddressRowStatus
dDhcpSExcludedAddressRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpServerUseClassEnabled.name: dDhcpServerUseClassEnabled
dDhcpServerUseClassEnabled.description: This object enables/disables the DHCP server to use DHCP classes during address allocation or use DHCP classes option to locate the addresses.

dDhcpSClassTable.name: dDhcpSClassTable
dDhcpSClassTable.description: A list of classes for DHCP server. This table is used to create and delete DHCP class.

dDhcpSClassEntry.name: dDhcpSClassEntry
dDhcpSClassEntry.description: An entry in DHCP class table contaning objects for creating or deleting a class for the DHCP server or relay.

dDhcpSClassName.name: dDhcpSClassName
dDhcpSClassName.description: This object indicates the class name of the corresponding entry.

dDhcpSClassRowStatus.name: dDhcpSClassRowStatus
dDhcpSClassRowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows in this table and to delete existing rows.

dDhcpSClassOptionTable.name: dDhcpSClassOptionTable
dDhcpSClassOptionTable.description: A list of DHCP option configuratoins for DHCP Relay and Server classes.

dDhcpSClassOptionEntry.name: dDhcpSClassOptionEntry
dDhcpSClassOptionEntry.description: An entry contains a DHCP option configuration of a DHCP class.

dDhcpSClassOptionCode.name: dDhcpSClassOptionCode
dDhcpSClassOptionCode.description: This object indicates the DHCP option code. The list of supported option code is project dependent. The following are some common used option codes: 60: vendor class identifier; 61: Client identifier; 77: user class; 82: Relay agent information option; 124: vendor-identifying vendor class; 125: vendor-identifying vendor-specific information.

dDhcpSClassOptionPatternValue.name: dDhcpSClassOptionPatternValue
dDhcpSClassOptionPatternValue.description: This object indicates the pattern of the corresponding DHCP option. Multiple option patterns can be specified for a DHCP class.

dDhcpSClassOptionWildcardMatch.name: dDhcpSClassOptionWildcardMatch
dDhcpSClassOptionWildcardMatch.description: This object indicates whether matching the remaining bits of the option. A value of 'false' means the bit length of dDhcpSClassOptionPatternValue should be the same as bit length of the option.

dDhcpSClassOptionMaskValue.name: dDhcpSClassOptionMaskValue
dDhcpSClassOptionMaskValue.description: This object indicates the hex bit mask for masking of the dDhcpSClassOptionPatternValue. The masked pattern bits will be matched. The masked pattern of every octet only supports: '00'H - indicates the corresponding octet will not be checked. 'FF'H - indicates the corresponding input octet must be same as the value of dDhcpSClassOptionPatternValue. If this object is a zero length string means the mask is not specified, all octets specified by dDhcpSClassOptionPatternValue will be checked.

dDhcpSClassOptionRowStatus.name: dDhcpSClassOptionRowStatus
dDhcpSClassOptionRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpSPoolTable.name: dDhcpSPoolTable
dDhcpSPoolTable.description: This table is used to create and delete DHCP pool.

dDhcpSPoolEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolEntry
dDhcpSPoolEntry.description: An entry in DHCP Pool table contaning objects for creating or deleting a global pool for the DHCP server or relay.

dDhcpSPoolName.name: dDhcpSPoolName
dDhcpSPoolName.description: This object indicates the DHCP pool name of the corresponding entry.

dDhcpSPoolRowStatus.name: dDhcpSPoolRowStatus
dDhcpSPoolRowStatus.description: This object is used to create new rows in this table and to delete existing rows.

dDhcpSPoolCfgTable.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgTable
dDhcpSPoolCfgTable.description: A list of DHCP server pool informations.

dDhcpSPoolCfgEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgEntry
dDhcpSPoolCfgEntry.description: An entry contaning DHCP server pool information.

dDhcpSPoolCfgDomainName.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgDomainName
dDhcpSPoolCfgDomainName.description: The domain name for the client if the server allocates the address for the client from this pool.

dDhcpSPoolCfgNetBIOSNodeType.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgNetBIOSNodeType
dDhcpSPoolCfgNetBIOSNodeType.description: The NetBIOS node type for a Microsoft DHCP client. The value 'notSpecified' indicates NetBIOS node type is not configured for the corresponding entry.

dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseState.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseState
dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseState.description: The pool lease state. When configured to 'infinite', the following objects: dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseDay, dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseHour and dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseMinute will be reverted to default value and not be used for lease time.

dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseDay.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseDay
dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseDay.description: This object indicates the number of days for the duration of lease.

dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseHour.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseHour
dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseHour.description: This object indicates the number of hours for the duration of lease.

dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseMinute.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseMinute
dDhcpSPoolCfgLeaseMinute.description: This object indicates the number of minutes for the duration of lease.

dDhcpSPoolCfgBootFile.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgBootFile
dDhcpSPoolCfgBootFile.description: This object indicates the name of the file that is used as a boot image.

dDhcpSPoolCfgNextServer.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgNextServer
dDhcpSPoolCfgNextServer.description: This object indicates the next server to be used in the DHCP client boot process. The server is typically a TFTP server. A length of zero indicates the next server is unspecified.

dDhcpSPoolCfgVrfName.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgVrfName
dDhcpSPoolCfgVrfName.description: This object is used to configure the VRF for DHCP pool. The zero length string means the VRF name is not specified.

dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocTable.name: dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocTable
dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocTable.description: A list of information indicates the address allocation for DHCP server.

dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocEntry
dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocEntry.description: An entry contaning the network configuration for DHCP pool.

dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocNetwork.name: dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocNetwork
dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocNetwork.description: The network address of the corresponding entry. The number of network configuration can be supported in a pool is project dependent.

dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocNetworkMask.name: dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocNetworkMask
dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocNetworkMask.description: The network address mask of the corresponding entry.

dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocRowStatus.name: dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocRowStatus
dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpSPoolManualBindTable.name: dDhcpSPoolManualBindTable
dDhcpSPoolManualBindTable.description: A list of information indicates the manual binding information for DHCP pool.

dDhcpSPoolManualBindEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolManualBindEntry
dDhcpSPoolManualBindEntry.description: An entry contaning the manual binding information for DHCP pool.

dDhcpSPoolManualBindHostIp.name: dDhcpSPoolManualBindHostIp
dDhcpSPoolManualBindHostIp.description: This object indicates the IP address of the manual binding entry in a DHCP address pool. The user cannot configure the manual binding entry in the address pool that has been configured with network.

dDhcpSPoolManualBindHostIpMask.name: dDhcpSPoolManualBindHostIpMask
dDhcpSPoolManualBindHostIpMask.description: This object indicates the mask the network part of the host address.

dDhcpSPoolManualBindHAddr.name: dDhcpSPoolManualBindHAddr
dDhcpSPoolManualBindHAddr.description: This object indicates the hardware address of the manual binding entry in a DHCP address pool.

dDhcpSPoolManualBindClientId.name: dDhcpSPoolManualBindClientId
dDhcpSPoolManualBindClientId.description: This object indicates DHCP client ID of the manual binding entry in a DHCP address pool.

dDhcpSPoolManualBindRowStatus.name: dDhcpSPoolManualBindRowStatus
dDhcpSPoolManualBindRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpSPoolClassAddrTable.name: dDhcpSPoolClassAddrTable
dDhcpSPoolClassAddrTable.description: A table contains address range configuration of a DHCP pool class.

dDhcpSPoolClassAddrEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolClassAddrEntry
dDhcpSPoolClassAddrEntry.description: By using DHCP class, DHCP server using option configuration to further determine which IP addresses to allocate to clients. The first two index elements identify the pool class to which this address range belongs.

dDhcpSPoolClassAddrBeginAddr.name: dDhcpSPoolClassAddrBeginAddr
dDhcpSPoolClassAddrBeginAddr.description: The start address of this class address range. A special address 0.0.0.0 indicates there is no address range is configured for this pool class. When a valid address range is configured, the entry of 0.0.0.0 will be removed.

dDhcpSPoolClassAddrEndAddr.name: dDhcpSPoolClassAddrEndAddr
dDhcpSPoolClassAddrEndAddr.description: The end address of this class address range.

dDhcpSPoolClassAddrRowStatus.name: dDhcpSPoolClassAddrRowStatus
dDhcpSPoolClassAddrRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpSPoolOptionTable.name: dDhcpSPoolOptionTable
dDhcpSPoolOptionTable.description: A list of option configurations for DHCP pools.

dDhcpSPoolOptionEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolOptionEntry
dDhcpSPoolOptionEntry.description: An entry contaning a DHCP option configuration of a DHCP class.

dDhcpSPoolOptionCode.name: dDhcpSPoolOptionCode
dDhcpSPoolOptionCode.description: This object indicates the code of DHCP option. Some options can be configured by other objects (e.g. option 1 which is used to configure Subnet Mask can be configured by dDhcpSPoolAddrAllocEntry and then should not be configured by this object.

dDhcpSPoolOptionType.name: dDhcpSPoolOptionType
dDhcpSPoolOptionType.description: This object indicates the type of dDhcpSPoolOptionValue. string(1): The type of option value is character string. hex(2) : The type of option value is hexadecimal string. ip(3) : The type of option value is IP list.

dDhcpSPoolOptionValue.name: dDhcpSPoolOptionValue
dDhcpSPoolOptionValue.description: This object indicates the value of the corresponding DHCP option.

dDhcpSPoolOptionRowStatus.name: dDhcpSPoolOptionRowStatus
dDhcpSPoolOptionRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterTable.name: dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterTable
dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterTable.description: A list of default router IP configuration for DHCP client.

dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterEntry
dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterEntry.description: An entry contaning default router configuration.

dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterAddr.name: dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterAddr
dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterAddr.description: The address of the default router.

dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterRowStatus.name: dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterRowStatus
dDhcpSPoolDefaultRouterRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpSPoolDnsServerTable.name: dDhcpSPoolDnsServerTable
dDhcpSPoolDnsServerTable.description: A list of DNS server configurations.

dDhcpSPoolDnsServerEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolDnsServerEntry
dDhcpSPoolDnsServerEntry.description: An entry containing DNS server configuration for DHCP pool.

dDhcpSPoolDnsServerAddr.name: dDhcpSPoolDnsServerAddr
dDhcpSPoolDnsServerAddr.description: The address of the DNS server.

dDhcpSPoolDnsServerRowStatus.name: dDhcpSPoolDnsServerRowStatus
dDhcpSPoolDnsServerRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpSPoolWinsServerTable.name: dDhcpSPoolWinsServerTable
dDhcpSPoolWinsServerTable.description: A list of WINS (Windows Internet Name Service) server configurations.

dDhcpSPoolWinsServerEntry.name: dDhcpSPoolWinsServerEntry
dDhcpSPoolWinsServerEntry.description: An entry containing WINS server configuration.

dDhcpSPoolWinsServerIndex.name: dDhcpSPoolWinsServerIndex
dDhcpSPoolWinsServerIndex.description: The index of this WINS server.

dDhcpSPoolWinsServerAddr.name: dDhcpSPoolWinsServerAddr
dDhcpSPoolWinsServerAddr.description: The address of the WINS server.

dDhcpSPoolWinsServerRowStatus.name: dDhcpSPoolWinsServerRowStatus
dDhcpSPoolWinsServerRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcpServerClearStatistics.name: dDhcpServerClearStatistics
dDhcpServerClearStatistics.description: This object is used to reset all DHCP server counters when set to 'clear'. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dDhcpServerRecvBootRequest.name: dDhcpServerRecvBootRequest
dDhcpServerRecvBootRequest.description: The total number of received BootRequest packets.

dDhcpServerRecvMalformedPkt.name: dDhcpServerRecvMalformedPkt
dDhcpServerRecvMalformedPkt.description: The total number of received malformed packets.

dDhcpServerRecvRenewPkt.name: dDhcpServerRecvRenewPkt
dDhcpServerRecvRenewPkt.description: The total number of received packets used to extend leases.

dDhcpServerRecvDiscover.name: dDhcpServerRecvDiscover
dDhcpServerRecvDiscover.description: The total number of received DHCPDISCOVER packets.

dDhcpServerRecvRequest.name: dDhcpServerRecvRequest
dDhcpServerRecvRequest.description: The total number of received DHCPREQUEST packets.

dDhcpServerRecvDecline.name: dDhcpServerRecvDecline
dDhcpServerRecvDecline.description: The total number of received DHCPDECLINE packets.

dDhcpServerRecvRelease.name: dDhcpServerRecvRelease
dDhcpServerRecvRelease.description: The total number of received DHCPRELEASE packets.

dDhcpServerRecvInform.name: dDhcpServerRecvInform
dDhcpServerRecvInform.description: The total number of received DHCPRINFORM packets.

dDhcpServerSendBootReply.name: dDhcpServerSendBootReply
dDhcpServerSendBootReply.description: The total number of sent BootReply packets.

dDhcpServerSendOffer.name: dDhcpServerSendOffer
dDhcpServerSendOffer.description: The total number of sent DHCPOFFER packets.

dDhcpServerSendAck.name: dDhcpServerSendAck
dDhcpServerSendAck.description: The total number of sent DHCPACK packets.

dDhcpServerSendNak.name: dDhcpServerSendNak
dDhcpServerSendNak.description: The total number of sent DHCPNAK packets.

dDhcpServerBindingTable.name: dDhcpServerBindingTable
dDhcpServerBindingTable.description: A list of information regarding binding information of a pool of IP addresses.

dDhcpServerBindingVrfName.name: dDhcpServerBindingVrfName
dDhcpServerBindingVrfName.description: The name of virtual routing and forwarding(VRF). If this object is a zero length string, the corresponding entry is for global routing and forwarding space.

dDhcpServerBindingIpAddress.name: dDhcpServerBindingIpAddress
dDhcpServerBindingIpAddress.description: This object indicates the IP address which has been assigned to a specified client.

dDhcpSBindingHwAddrOrClientId.name: dDhcpSBindingHwAddrOrClientId
dDhcpSBindingHwAddrOrClientId.description: This object indicates the hardware address or client identifier of the DHCP client. The first octet of this object contains the hardware type of the DHCP client. The remaining octets contain the hardware address of the client. If the first octet is 0 (zero) indicates the remaining octets contain other than a hardware address. For more information about the client identifier, please see RFC 2132, DHCP Options and BOOTP Vendor Extensions, section 9.14.

dDhcpServerBindingLeaseExpire.name: dDhcpServerBindingLeaseExpire
dDhcpServerBindingLeaseExpire.description: This object indicates the expiration of the lease expiration time of the binding entry. The special value of all '00'Hs indicates that the lease will never be expired (infinite).

dDhcpServerBindingClear.name: dDhcpServerBindingClear
dDhcpServerBindingClear.description: This object is used to clear this entry. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. The value of this object when read is always 'noOp'.

dDhcpSConflictIpTable.name: dDhcpSConflictIpTable
dDhcpSConflictIpTable.description: A list of conflict IP addresses while DHCP Server attempts to assign the IP address to client.

dDhcpSConflictIpEntry.name: dDhcpSConflictIpEntry
dDhcpSConflictIpEntry.description: A DHCP address conflict means a duplication of use of the same IP address by two hosts.

dDhcpSConflictIpVrfName.name: dDhcpSConflictIpVrfName
dDhcpSConflictIpVrfName.description: The name of virtual routing and forwarding (VRF). If this object is zero length string, the corresponding entry is for global routing and forwarding space.

dDhcpSConflictIpAddr.name: dDhcpSConflictIpAddr
dDhcpSConflictIpAddr.description: This object indicates the IP address which is duplicated and used by more than one host.

dDhcpSConflictIpDetectMethod.name: dDhcpSConflictIpDetectMethod
dDhcpSConflictIpDetectMethod.description: The server detects conflicts using ping. The client detects conflicts using gratuitous Address Resolution Protocol (ARP).

dDhcpSConflictIpDetectTime.name: dDhcpSConflictIpDetectTime
dDhcpSConflictIpDetectTime.description: The time at which a DHCP address conflict detected.

dDhcpSConflictIpClear.name: dDhcpSConflictIpClear
dDhcpSConflictIpClear.description: This object is used to clear this entry. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. The value of this object when read is always 'noOp'.

dDhcpServerCompliance.name: dDhcpServerCompliance
dDhcpServerCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the DLINKSW-DHCP-SERVER-MIB.

dDhcpSGblCfgGroup.name: dDhcpSGblCfgGroup
dDhcpSGblCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing global configuration about DHCP server.

dDhcpSClassGroup.name: dDhcpSClassGroup
dDhcpSClassGroup.description: A collection of objects providing DHCP class configuration.

dDhcpSClassCfgGroup.name: dDhcpSClassCfgGroup
dDhcpSClassCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing DHCP relay agent configuration of a class or address range of a class under a DHCP pool.

dDhcpSPoolGroup.name: dDhcpSPoolGroup
dDhcpSPoolGroup.description: This group is used to create/delete DHCP pools.

dDhcpSPoolCfgGroup.name: dDhcpSPoolCfgGroup
dDhcpSPoolCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing DHCP pool configuration.

dDhcpSPoolNetworkCfgGroup.name: dDhcpSPoolNetworkCfgGroup
dDhcpSPoolNetworkCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing network configuration for DHCP pools.

dDhcpSPoolManualBindingGroup.name: dDhcpSPoolManualBindingGroup
dDhcpSPoolManualBindingGroup.description: A collection of objects providing manual binding configuration for DHCP pools.

dDhcpSStatisticsGroup.name: dDhcpSStatisticsGroup
dDhcpSStatisticsGroup.description: A collection of objects for management of DHCP statistics.

dDhcpSGeneralInfoGroup.name: dDhcpSGeneralInfoGroup
dDhcpSGeneralInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects providing general DHCP information, e.g binding database, conflict IP address.
